====Verb====
{{en-verb|+|+|wove|past2=weaved|woven|past_ptc2=weaved|past_ptc3=wove|past_ptc3_qual=now colloquial and nonstandard}}

# To form something by passing lengths or [[strand]]s of [[material]] over and under one another.
#: {{ux|en|This loom '''weaves''' yarn into sweaters.}}
# To [[spin]] a [[cocoon]] or a [[web]].
#: {{ux|en|Spiders '''weave''' beautiful but deadly webs.}}
# To [[unite]] by close [[connection]] or [[intermixture]].
#* {{RQ:Shakespeare King Lear|II|i|passage=This '''weaves''' itself, perforce, into my business.}}
#* {{RQ:Byron Childe Harold|canto=III|stanza=CII|passage=these words, thus '''woven''' into song}}
# To compose creatively and intricately; to fabricate.
#: {{ux|en|to '''weave''' the plot of a story}}

